  "title": "Environmental Control Officer (ECO)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p>\n<p>• Ensure compliance with latest environmental regulations.</p>\n<p>• Conduct regular inspection to ensure ECM and environmental plan are in place.</p>\n<p>• Manage noise monitoring plan and report / manage vector and air pollution control plan.</p>\n<p>• Safety matters on site.</p>\n<p>• Actively involved in site works and inspections and ECO programs.</p>\n<p>• Ensure safety &amp; environmental compliance.</p>\n<p>• Prepare and submit weekly report.</p>\n<p>• Liaise with government authorities.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirement</strong></p>\n<p>• Candidate must possess at least a recognized Diploma in relevant trade.</p>\n<p>• Min 3 years of experience as ECO in Construction sector.</p>\n<p>• Must registered ECO with NEA.</p>\n<p>• ECMO certified.</p>\n<p>• Preferably with LTA project.</p>\n<p>• Work well under pressure and work independently.</p>\n<p>• Familiar with Occupational Safety, Health and Environmental regulations.</p>\n<p><br></p>",
